[b][size=150]Usage[/size][/b]
The images are stored inside the Help tab of this button (one image per line). Left-clicking on this button will switch between its enabled/disabled state. More than one version of this button can be installed at the same time containing different sets of icons. It will also work for buttons edited in tabs (See [url=https://github.com/Infocatcher/Custom_Buttons/tree/master/Edit_Custom_Button_in_Tab]Edit Custom Button in Tab[/url] button by [b]InfoCatcher[/b] or [url=http://custombuttons.sourceforge.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=4&t=3599]Custom Buttons Context Menu Extended[/url]).

[img]https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/5194280/0PublishedCB/CustomIconsForCBEditor/CustomIconsForCBEditor001.png[/img]

[b][size=150]Compatibility[/size][/b]
Tested and working on Firefox Stable/Dev. Edition, SeaMonkey and Palemoon.
[b][color=#FF0000]Not compatible with Nightly nor Windows Vista[/color][/b]

